What is it?

769
01:01:04,597 --> 01:01:06,169
A beetle.

770
01:01:07,358 --> 01:01:10,214
You've been like this for two hours.
What's the matter?

771
01:01:11,145 --> 01:01:13,007
Nothing's the matter.

772
01:01:14,162 --> 01:01:15,928
Where's the cat?

773
01:01:25,848 --> 01:01:27,839
Did she sleep with you?

774
01:01:28,673 --> 01:01:31,049
Does it annoy you?
And you, do you find it amusing?

775
01:01:34,387 --> 01:01:36,121
You have a side that's very superficial.

776
01:02:10,727 --> 01:02:13,808
I always dreamed of having something
with an especially inept employee...

777
01:02:15,172 --> 01:02:16,391
Fire her...

778
01:02:17,191 --> 01:02:18,991
and escape with her.

779
01:02:22,885 --> 01:02:25,454
I promise, once my three months notice
are through, we'll go together

780
01:02:27,774 --> 01:02:29,346
...somewhere.

781
01:02:30,146 --> 01:02:31,346
And after that?

782
01:02:34,739 --> 01:02:35,999
Then we'll come back...

783
01:02:38,200 --> 01:02:40,558
Come back.

784
01:02:48,607 --> 01:02:50,277
Another coffee?

785
01:02:51,271 --> 01:02:54,963
I'd like to know how was it
that I was picked for this?

786
01:02:55,406 --> 01:02:57,493
Let's say a computer did it.

787
01:02:58,262 --> 01:02:59,900
Out of millions, obviously.
- Of course.

788
01:03:00,100 --> 01:03:01,300
Good afternoon.
- Good afternoon.

789
01:03:01,699 --> 01:03:03,463
Our oldest employee.

790
01:03:04,267 --> 01:03:05,870
Maybe he's the computer
who picked me.

791
01:03:10,333 --> 01:03:13,094
This will do it good.
It needs refreshment.

792
01:03:13,928 --> 01:03:16,336
Could you imagine being buried
all alone in this cold dirt?

793
01:03:17,652 --> 01:03:22,051
You could do a guide to graveyards.
It would be a best-seller.

794
01:03:22,756 --> 01:03:26,067
Luceram cemetery. One shinbone.
Modest, but good location.

795
01:03:26,480 --> 01:03:29,724
Another one: Three shinbones.
Worth a detour.

796
01:03:30,333 --> 01:03:32,901
No shinbone.
Avoid.

797
01:03:33,447 --> 01:03:36,143
I'd rather live here
than die here.

798
01:03:37,332 --> 01:03:39,407
These situations only
occur in books.

799
01:03:39,607 --> 01:03:42,707
And when they occur, one doesn't take advantage.
- That's still to be seen.

800
01:03:52,612 --> 01:03:54,698
I don't mean
to scare you.

801
01:03:57,330 --> 01:03:58,781
I killed Catherine in Glasgow
two months ago.

802
01:04:01,601 --> 01:04:03,911
I went with her
without telling anybody...

803
01:04:04,585 --> 01:04:06,512
...and I came back alone.

804
01:04:07,474 --> 01:04:09,144
I don't believe it.

805
01:04:09,626 --> 01:04:11,320
You're right and wrong.

806
01:04:11,420 --> 01:04:12,574
What does that mean?

807
01:04:12,575 --> 01:04:16,051
You're right, I'm not capable of killing,
but you're wrong...

808
01:04:16,251 --> 01:04:17,451
...because I still did it.

809
01:04:17,510 --> 01:04:18,775
Impossible.

810
01:04:19,375 --> 01:04:21,675
That's what I thought too.

811
01:04:23,875 --> 01:04:26,375
That day, it was very cold
in Glasgow.

812
01:04:27,075 --> 01:04:29,075
Catherine had never gone
that far before.

813
01:04:30,275 --> 01:04:31,475
Me either.

814
01:04:31,554 --> 01:04:33,195
She didn't like the city;
she thought it gloomy.

815
01:04:35,603 --> 01:04:39,060
I think I'd never seen Catherine as
depressed as she was that day.

816
01:04:43,494 --> 01:04:45,548
She was absolutely...

817
01:04:58,700 --> 01:05:00,945
We haven't slept
all night.

818
01:05:01,268 --> 01:05:03,321
I'll be exhausted tomorrow.

819
01:05:03,643 --> 01:05:05,664
Let's try to sleep a little.

820
01:05:11,733 --> 01:05:15,873
It's strange to wake up exactly
when I was planning to sleep again.

821
01:05:31,829 --> 01:05:33,818
She was asleep.

822
01:05:35,231 --> 01:05:38,697
And the strange thing was
that she was smiling... in her sleep.

823
01:05:40,285 --> 01:05:44,041
I'd never seen he smiling in
her sleep. It was the first time.

824
01:05:46,242 --> 01:05:49,935
She looked relaxed... happy.

825
01:05:54,363 --> 01:05:56,264
That's how it all happened.

826
01:06:02,390 --> 01:06:04,027
I looked at Catherine...

827
01:06:04,902 --> 01:06:06,539
29 minutes.

828
01:06:07,727 --> 01:06:09,492
What have you decided?

829
01:06:11,692 --> 01:06:12,792
And the risks?

830
01:06:12,800 --> 01:06:16,036
We must try whatever we can
because the T.5. is no longer working.

831
01:06:18,063 --> 01:06:19,669
Are you Mr. Ridder?

832
01:06:20,569 --> 01:06:21,569
Yes, that's me.

833
01:06:21,715 --> 01:06:24,219
Wiana went out.
She went to the post-office.

834
01:06:24,419 --> 01:06:25,819
That's alright. I'll wait.

835
01:06:26,571 --> 01:06:28,594
Come in
if you like.

836
01:06:29,075 --> 01:06:30,808
We're two girls here
in the bathroom.

837
01:06:31,065 --> 01:06:34,211
Which one will you take?
The one on the right or on the left?

838
01:06:36,483 --> 01:06:37,487
The left one.

839
01:06:38,387 --> 01:06:39,387
Or if not...

840
01:06:40,187 --> 01:06:42,287
No. The one on the left.

841
01:06:43,987 --> 01:06:45,687
You chose badly.

842
01:06:45,784 --> 01:06:50,773
I'm Nicole. I arrived yesterday.
Do you mind if I take a bath?

843
01:06:51,115 --> 01:06:54,966
Wash my back
while we talk.

844
01:06:55,913 --> 01:06:57,824
What do you do
at the office?

845
01:07:01,113 --> 01:07:02,814
Sometimes I think.

846
01:07:03,038 --> 01:07:05,607
I pick up an object
and I start to think.

847
01:07:06,667 --> 01:07:09,492
Here is a pen.

848
01:07:09,692 --> 01:07:12,092
I concentrate and I see
that it's a red pencil.

849
01:07:13,794 --> 01:07:15,526
It's red on the outside
but it writes black.

850
01:07:15,705 --> 01:07:17,277
Proof that appearances
are deceiving.

851
01:07:18,705 --> 01:07:21,123
It's of normal size;
a common pencil...

852
01:07:21,370 --> 01:07:24,418
...of the kind found everywhere.

853
01:07:26,282 --> 01:07:27,886
It has a point...

854
01:07:28,592 --> 01:07:30,390
...like a pencil.

855
01:07:31,482 --> 01:07:35,237
When you push it,
It rolls...

856
01:07:35,943 --> 01:07:38,031
...like a pencil, naturally.

857
01:07:38,575 --> 01:07:40,919
If you hold it up...

858
01:07:41,240 --> 01:07:44,033
...it looks like the trunk
of a tree, smooth and straight ...

859
01:07:45,286 --> 01:07:47,468
In the same way,
it also looks like a pencil.

860
01:07:47,468 --> 01:07:49,468
So it would seem that
we are dealing with a pencil

861
01:07:49,542 --> 01:07:52,141
On the other hand,
I never use a pencil

862
01:07:52,518 --> 01:07:54,112
Why would I have one
in this case?

863
01:07:54,162 --> 01:07:59,073
Doubtless because tables
are meant for holding pencils.

864
01:08:02,085 --> 01:08:04,301
I like your story.
Keep going.

865
01:08:04,401 --> 01:08:06,201
There are other things
apart from pencils.

866
01:08:06,617 --> 01:08:08,829
There are also erasers,
pads, paper...

867
01:08:09,780 --> 01:08:10,941
She has received over
150 letters of complaint.

868
01:08:10,941 --> 01:08:12,141
And she has them piled up there.

869
01:08:12,250 --> 01:08:13,920
They said there were 300 letters
that were late.

870
01:08:14,320 --> 01:08:15,296
And now?

871
01:08:15,297 --> 01:08:18,026
We've caught up.
- Even a bit ahead.

872
01:08:18,926 --> 01:08:21,126
Claude told me this morning
that he'd responded to a letter...

873
01:08:21,521 --> 01:08:23,559
...that we haven't got yet.

874
01:08:23,617 --> 01:08:27,988
I'm absolutely exhausted.
I hardly slept 3 hours last night.

875
01:08:28,188 --> 01:08:31,288
And besides that, I dreamed
that I had to do 100 pages.

876
01:08:35,132 --> 01:08:36,705
It's going to be a nice day.

877
01:08:38,305 --> 01:08:40,305
One knows these things by the sea.

878
01:08:44,667 --> 01:08:48,840
If people are up, it's...

879
01:08:49,803 --> 01:08:51,536
Everything's ready.

880
01:08:52,974 --> 01:08:56,377
Is it much?
- 5 whole years.

881
01:08:57,186 --> 01:08:58,856
It'll be a few days.

882
01:09:16,062 --> 01:09:19,144
Even though I make love to other girls,
I feel drawn to you.

883
01:09:19,753 --> 01:09:22,483
It's hurtful that you do it
with other girls.

884
01:09:24,634 --> 01:09:26,999
I don't know what to say.

885
01:09:30,399 --> 01:09:31,699
Do you understand?

886
01:09:33,559 --> 01:09:36,704
Yes, Claude, I do.
That's why I'm sad.

887
01:09:37,379 --> 01:09:39,562
If Prometheus didn't have
his vulture...

888
01:09:39,571 --> 01:09:41,272
Speaking of vultures,
I bought a chicken for tonight.

889
01:09:42,092 --> 01:09:46,014
I don't know what to do.
I can't get down to work.

890
01:09:46,456 --> 01:09:48,222
Move about, I don't know,
do something.

891
01:09:49,673 --> 01:09:52,531
What did I do this morning?
I kept watching the telephone.

892
01:09:53,522 --> 01:09:55,447
What does that girl have?

893
01:09:55,662 --> 01:09:57,587
Nothing.
But I want her.

894
01:10:01,584 --> 01:10:04,376
I'd do anything for her.

895
01:10:04,882 --> 01:10:08,028
Including sending Catherine to hell.

896
01:10:08,773 --> 01:10:10,192
Well, call her.

897
01:10:10,581 --> 01:10:12,828
I don't have her number.

898
01:10:13,278 --> 01:10:15,943
All I can do is wait.

899
01:10:16,921 --> 01:10:18,133
A kiss?

900
01:10:18,333 --> 01:10:20,433
I won't be able to stand it.
- I'd like it very much.

901
01:10:36,524 --> 01:10:38,774
He's all right.
- He's completely immobilised.

902
01:10:46,253 --> 01:10:48,340
Let's wait a bit longer.

903
01:10:48,347 --> 01:10:50,352
The minute flees,
but I look for it.

904
01:10:51,329 --> 01:10:53,640
I concentrate on
that minute.

905
01:10:54,860 --> 01:10:58,712
I'm in the water.
The sun's hot...

906
01:11:00,800 --> 01:11:04,009
Catherine is there, on the beach.

907
01:11:05,808 --> 01:11:06,528
The water's warm...

908
01:11:07,428 --> 01:11:08,628
I swim in it.

909
01:11:10,428 --> 01:11:11,628
I see the bottom.

910
01:11:27,766 --> 01:11:29,595
I want to swim.

911
01:11:33,395 --> 01:11:34,295
Thank you.

912
01:11:35,214 --> 01:11:38,386
Sorry, I don't speak French.

913
01:11:38,586 --> 01:11:40,786
But you understand English, I hope.

914
01:11:41,086 --> 01:11:42,686
Yes, without a problem.

915
01:11:43,239 --> 01:11:45,229
Then where is Catherine?

916
01:11:53,729 --> 01:11:55,629
Catherine!

917
01:12:03,028 --> 01:12:05,921
In the end...
- Yes, in the end...

918
01:12:06,802 --> 01:12:08,183
Nothing...

919
01:12:08,784 --> 01:12:10,164
Do you have to go?

920
01:12:10,512 --> 01:12:11,736
I should.

921
01:12:13,989 --> 01:12:15,916
Stay with me.

922
01:12:17,583 --> 01:12:19,736
I can't find an excuse
every day.

923
01:12:20,988 --> 01:12:23,913
I'll write you an encyclopaedia
with all the excuses you can use.

924
01:12:24,775 --> 01:12:26,413
You're already late.

925
01:12:26,787 --> 01:12:30,185
Like every day, punctually late,
never more than an hour.

926
01:12:30,529 --> 01:12:31,617
And occasionally less.

927
01:12:33,732 --> 01:12:35,432
Seen many fish?

928
01:12:35,978 --> 01:12:37,873
2 sea snakes,
some sharks...

929
01:12:38,322 --> 01:12:40,377
Nothing at all.

930
01:12:42,367 --> 01:12:44,262
Nothing changes.

931
01:12:49,366 --> 01:12:51,055
It's strange.

932
01:12:51,256 --> 01:12:52,843
I'm going to die.

933
01:12:58,150 --> 01:13:00,317
Catherine...

934
01:13:01,217 --> 01:13:02,517
Do you realise?

935
01:13:04,133 --> 01:13:06,219
...you were right.

936
01:13:15,419 --> 01:13:16,619
Catherine...

937
01:13:21,849 --> 01:13:23,290
I'd like to see the mouse.

938
01:13:23,970 --> 01:13:25,930
He's coming back more often.

939
01:13:26,410 --> 01:13:28,176
An interval of 30 seconds
since last time.

940
01:13:28,690 --> 01:13:30,392
That's not much.

941
01:13:35,785 --> 01:13:38,385
A storm at 7 a.m.
is unusual.

942
01:13:39,701 --> 01:13:41,563
People get up early.

943
01:13:41,663 --> 01:13:42,863
Who?

944
01:13:44,099 --> 01:13:46,860
God... the workers...

945
01:13:47,824 --> 01:13:50,110
You don't understand...
- Not today.

946
01:13:51,856 --> 01:13:54,429
You're lucky.
You're all blind.

947
01:13:55,272 --> 01:13:58,193
People are scared because they have
a hard life, discouraging.

948
01:13:58,706 --> 01:14:00,729
In those moments, they should be
convinced of the reverse.

949
01:14:00,974 --> 01:14:03,060
I doubt it. It won't last.

950
01:14:03,431 --> 01:14:05,134
Finally, it goes by fast.

951
01:14:06,603 --> 01:14:08,433
When you're okay,
that's when it's scary...

952
01:14:09,075 --> 01:14:11,547
You know that one day it'll all be lost,
and it's unsupportable.

953
01:14:11,889 --> 01:14:13,593
It's unsupportable,
and the rest doesn't matter.

954
01:14:15,777 --> 01:14:17,574
When you're hungry,
time drags...

955
01:14:18,321 --> 01:14:20,953
It takes 3 months or 60 years to die...

956
01:14:20,953 --> 01:14:22,453
It's strange, isn't it?

957
01:14:22,566 --> 01:14:25,347
One even adapts to cancer.

958
01:14:27,758 --> 01:14:29,235
Choose something...

959
01:14:32,124 --> 01:14:35,142
Carrots are good
for the skin.

960
01:14:35,719 --> 01:14:38,513
After... Spinach for influenza...

961
01:14:39,058 --> 01:14:42,236
Fruit, of course,
is good for your health.

962
01:14:42,360 --> 01:14:44,769
I don't think I can help you.

963
01:14:46,064 --> 01:14:47,437
I wish I'd never met you.

964
01:14:47,613 --> 01:14:51,242
That can't be changed.

965
01:14:58,969 --> 01:15:02,853
Something to drink?
- I can't drink; it makes me sleepy.

966
01:15:05,164 --> 01:15:07,026
Have you been
here long?

967
01:15:08,226 --> 01:15:10,226
Hello, how are you?

968
01:15:23,335 --> 01:15:25,453
There it is; we can work now.

969
01:15:25,742 --> 01:15:27,314
We haven't brought
all the documents.

970
01:15:28,928 --> 01:15:33,678
Hello, cat...
I'm happy to see you.

971
01:15:34,290 --> 01:15:36,279
Have you eaten well today?

972
01:15:37,035 --> 01:15:40,053
'I tell you this woman doesn't
give me enough to eat.'

973
01:15:42,347 --> 01:15:44,305
Yes, I think she's a bit stingy.

974
01:15:44,595 --> 01:15:46,858
'Stingy.'

975
01:15:47,159 --> 01:15:49,420
But on the street, you'd have
less to eat.

976
01:15:50,361 --> 01:15:52,576
'That's no reason for me to starve
in an apartment.'

977
01:15:53,476 --> 01:15:55,369
You exaggerate.

978
01:15:55,883 --> 01:15:58,066
'You won't believe me
if I don't exaggerate.'

979
01:15:59,093 --> 01:16:01,403
'I don't like your records.'

980
01:16:02,016 --> 01:16:04,658
'They're noisy and all
sound the same.'

981
01:16:05,186 --> 01:16:07,692
'I had more fun outside.
I had friends there.'

982
01:16:09,233 --> 01:16:12,181
We're your friends.
You can chat with us.

983
01:16:12,551 --> 01:16:15,079
'But you're not very smart.'

984
01:16:15,658 --> 01:16:17,951
Sophie thinks we are.

985
01:16:19,002 --> 01:16:21,161
What are you reading?

986
01:16:25,861 --> 01:16:27,261
Where did you find this?

987
01:16:27,616 --> 01:16:29,414
What does that mean?
- I don't know.

988
01:16:29,695 --> 01:16:31,705
It bores me to explain.

989
01:16:33,572 --> 01:16:35,403
I couldn't care less.

990
01:16:35,903 --> 01:16:37,103
Why do you say that?

991
01:16:37,128 --> 01:16:39,352
I don't understand this.
It has nothing to do with me.

992
01:16:40,333 --> 01:16:42,053
And with you?
Not me either.

993
01:16:44,387 --> 01:16:47,876
Then it's a bit silly, a bit sad,
depends on how you look at it.

994
01:16:49,532 --> 01:16:52,073
I'm getting mixed up...

995
01:17:08,227 --> 01:17:11,183
I like you a lot.
I like you more than a lot.

996
01:17:13,380 --> 01:17:15,896
You can't say 'more than a lot'.

997
01:17:16,378 --> 01:17:19,368
You can't say it.
- But I can think it, right?

998
01:17:25,609 --> 01:17:29,832
I used to wake up at night.
I hated it.

999
01:17:31,346 --> 01:17:34,438
I stayed awake
so as not to wake up.

1000
01:17:36,271 --> 01:17:39,283
But now it's over.

1001
01:17:39,840 --> 01:17:41,884
I sleep until morning.

1002
01:17:42,584 --> 01:17:44,458
I sleep well, don't I?

1003
01:17:51,215 --> 01:17:53,184
Did you ever think
of killing Catherine?

1004
01:17:53,184 --> 01:17:54,084
Many times.

1005
01:17:56,608 --> 01:17:59,578
I believe it.
- Do you?

1006
01:18:03,157 --> 01:18:05,630
I thought all night about
what you told me.

1007
01:18:07,193 --> 01:18:09,231
I think you told the truth.

1008
01:18:10,332 --> 01:18:13,168
It's possible you've killed her
without anybody knowing.

1009
01:18:13,236 --> 01:18:16,609
And do you know why?

1010
01:18:18,720 --> 01:18:20,886
To end it all.

1011
01:18:22,459 --> 01:18:23,970
To end her suffering.

1012
01:18:26,670 --> 01:18:28,570
As you told me,

1013
01:18:28,875 --> 01:18:31,803
She had an incurable,
mortal illness, didn't she?

1014
01:18:31,952 --> 01:18:33,776
The periods vary.

1015
01:18:34,226 --> 01:18:35,665
We can't do anything.

1016
01:18:36,201 --> 01:18:37,680
Then everything is lost.

1017
01:18:40,806 --> 01:18:43,037
I went there to see a writer.
I was there for that.

1018
01:18:44,912 --> 01:18:47,753
We found a room
in a little hotel.

1019
01:18:49,105 --> 01:18:52,145
We turned on the gas heater
because it was a bit chilly.

1020
01:18:52,646 --> 01:18:54,230
She'd taken a sleeping pill.

1021
01:18:56,906 --> 01:18:58,710
When I saw her,
she was asleep,

1022
01:19:00,468 --> 01:19:04,160
The strange thing was that
she was smiling... asleep.

1023
01:19:08,052 --> 01:19:11,380
I'd never seen her smiling in her sleep.
It was the first time.

1024
01:19:12,418 --> 01:19:16,321
She looked relaxed... happy.

1025
01:19:18,656 --> 01:19:20,798
No longer afraid of anything.

1026
01:19:23,349 --> 01:19:25,210
That's how it all happened.

1027
01:19:29,117 --> 01:19:32,523
When I was going out I noticed
that the room was very cold.

1028
01:19:32,623 --> 01:19:34,023
Very cold.

1029
01:19:36,097 --> 01:19:37,966
I smelled gas...

1030
01:19:40,565 --> 01:19:43,481
The heater was off,
but the gas was on...

1031
01:19:43,781 --> 01:19:44,981
That was all.

1032
01:19:49,084 --> 01:19:52,234
I looked at her, smiling in her sleep,
and then I left.

1033
01:19:54,351 --> 01:19:57,094
When I came back an hour later,
she was dead.

1034
01:19:57,537 --> 01:19:59,371
The cops were already there.

1035
01:20:01,022 --> 01:20:04,195
Claude, I don't know why
you're lying to me.

1036
01:20:06,048 --> 01:20:07,868
Why didn't they arrest you?

1037
01:20:09,733 --> 01:20:11,721
They thought it was an accident.

1038
01:20:11,721 --> 01:20:12,721
Just like that?

1039
01:20:13,904 --> 01:20:15,791
It really was an accident.

1040
01:20:17,524 --> 01:20:19,934
I lied to see if
you'd believe me.

1041
01:20:21,427 --> 01:20:24,623
The heater must have
turned off while I was outside.

1042
01:20:25,223 --> 01:20:27,023
I returned...

1043
01:20:27,223 --> 01:20:28,423
...later...

1044
01:20:29,223 --> 01:20:30,423
...that night.

1045
01:20:30,723 --> 01:20:31,923
Much later.

1046
01:20:37,635 --> 01:20:39,737
She really died there?

1047
01:20:40,137 --> 01:20:41,337
Yes.

1048
01:20:43,542 --> 01:20:46,204
For a moment I was glad...

1049
01:20:47,707 --> 01:20:50,077
...though it was horrible,
I was glad.

1050
01:20:51,411 --> 01:20:54,821
Everything happened while she was asleep.
She didn't have to experience her death...

1051
01:20:57,420 --> 01:20:59,855
Then I realized she was
no longer there,

1052
01:21:01,646 --> 01:21:03,779
that she would never be there again.

1053
01:21:05,407 --> 01:21:07,391
And I couldn't stand it.

1054
01:21:12,680 --> 01:21:14,852
It got worse and worse.

1055
01:21:34,616 --> 01:21:37,065
What's wrong?
- Nothing.

1056
01:21:38,138 --> 01:21:40,064
George is dead.

1057
01:21:40,164 --> 01:21:41,364
Which George?

1058
01:21:41,364 --> 01:21:43,464
Slovain.
He's dead.

1059
01:21:44,149 --> 01:21:46,538
I know already.
He died 8 months ago.

1060
01:21:47,222 --> 01:21:48,945
You knew it?

1061
01:21:49,045 --> 01:21:50,527
Eight months ago.

1062
01:21:50,828 --> 01:21:53,183
His wife wrote me
a little after his death.

1063
01:21:53,366 --> 01:21:54,905
And you didn't tell me at all?

1064
01:21:57,401 --> 01:21:59,694
You were depressed,
so I didn't tell you.

1065
01:22:01,551 --> 01:22:03,604
Can you imagine a man...

1066
01:22:03,941 --> 01:22:06,296
...who, to spare his wife...

1067
01:22:07,106 --> 01:22:09,931
...would hide all bad news from her.

1068
01:22:10,789 --> 01:22:13,083
He'd hire actors to replace

1069
01:22:13,611 --> 01:22:16,106
...the people who had died.

1070
01:22:17,547 --> 01:22:24,577
He'd buy all the newspapers so that
she couldn't get one.

1071
01:22:29,001 --> 01:22:31,048
He'd have to cover up
the whole planet.

1072
01:22:32,270 --> 01:22:33,966
It would cost a lot.

1073
01:22:34,667 --> 01:22:36,360
It's ghastly.

1074
01:22:39,586 --> 01:22:41,167
What?

1075
01:22:41,894 --> 01:22:43,609
Everything.

1076
01:22:45,507 --> 01:22:47,391
Even when you're
with me.

1077
01:22:51,621 --> 01:22:55,683
Page 8, first line, put
"Evarista Corriego" in italics.

1078
01:22:56,661 --> 01:22:58,912
Same page, ninth line
after 'the words'...

1079
01:22:59,373 --> 01:23:01,537
the word "conjugated" is lacking.

1080
01:23:01,637 --> 01:23:02,837
With an acute accent and plural.

1081
01:23:04,195 --> 01:23:06,308
Page 9 is all right.

1082
01:23:06,308 --> 01:23:07,508
Page 10, twelfth line.

1083
01:23:08,008 --> 01:23:10,708
'Tln' with diaeresis over the 'o'.

1084
01:23:11,626 --> 01:23:13,111
Same page, 14th line...

1085
01:23:13,311 --> 01:23:16,711
It has 'solipsism' with 'c' instead of 's'.

1086
01:23:17,557 --> 01:23:20,066
Yes, it looks strange, but that's
how it is.  Page 11 all okay.

1087
01:23:20,690 --> 01:23:25,167
Page 12, eighth, no, ninth line:

1088
01:23:25,468 --> 01:23:27,943
"visual and tactile."

1089
01:25:56,647 --> 01:25:58,701
It's been more than an hour now.

1090
01:26:03,191 --> 01:26:05,314
We'll never get him back.

1091
01:26:57,649 --> 01:26:58,923
His pulse is weak.

1092
01:27:00,331 --> 01:27:02,224
He's lost
a lot of blood.

1093
01:27:05,712 --> 01:27:07,520
Can we move him?

1094
01:27:07,842 --> 01:27:09,948
Call the hospital, quick.

1095
01:27:16,660 --> 01:27:18,433
We'll have to check
all our figures.